How Listenwise Works









Listening is powerful.
Why practice listening?  Because listening comprehension is fundamental to literacy.
Research shows that if you are not a good listener, you won’t be a good reader. And since students can generally listen 2-3 grade levels above what they can read, we can use the power of listening to introduce more complex language, vocabulary and topics.

Get Started for Free 












Compelling podcasts for English, Social Studies, Science and ESL
Want good listeners? Tell a great story!
Learn More








Listening Comprehension Assessment
How well can your students listen? Can they distill main idea or make inferences?
Learn More








Listenwise Plans and Features
Compare our plans and learn more about the program features.
Learn More








Listenwise in the Classroom 
How do teachers use Listenwise? Blended learning in action.
